==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Accolade
<hw>Ac`co*lade"</hw> <pr>(⟦acr⟧k`k⟦osl⟧*l⟦amac⟧d" <it>or</it>
⟦acr⟧k`k⟦osl⟧*l⟦adot⟧d"; 277)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F.
<ets>accolade</ets>, It. <ets>accolata</ets>, fr. <ets>accollare</ets>
to embrace; L. <ets>ad</ets> + <ets>collum</ets> neck.]</ety>
<sn>1.</sn> <def>A ceremony formerly used in conferring knighthood,
consisting of an embrace, and a slight blow on the shoulders with the
flat blade of a sword.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Mus.)</fld> <def>A brace used to join two or more
staves.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Accombination</ent>⟦br⟧
